		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Diegesis</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Diegesis</b> is</p>
<ol>
<li>the (fictional) world in which the situations and events narrated occur; and</li>
<li>telling, recounting, as opposed to showing, enacting.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
</ol>
<p>In diegesis the <a href="/wiki/Narrator" title="Narrator">narrator</a> <i>tells</i> the story. The narrator presents to the audience or the implied readers the actions, and perhaps thoughts, of the characters.</p>
